South America
---
Brazil fatality (Recife, Pernambuco state). 31 Jan 2016. Dengue (reported) A 17-year-old female of the indigenous Xucururu tribe was proclaimed dead on 7 Jan 2016 at Restoration Hospital in the northeastern city of Recife in Pernambuco state due to acute myositis, which is a condition characterized by muscle pain, swelling and difficulty in walking. The death of the girl was the 1st reported fatal case in Brazil and only the 5th in the world due to this rare condition.
http://www.latinoshealth.com/articles/17805/20160131/first-death-chikungunya-virus-reported-brazil-same-mosquito-carrying-zika.htm

